<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-01T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-01T23:00:00-05:00" n="961" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d961">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.111/480: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-02T13:00:00+09:00">July 2,
                                    1941—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 6—7:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>917. Peiping’s 147, June 26, 1 p.m., North China travel restrictions.
                            This Embassy sent to the Foreign Office a third person note dated June
                            30 requesting that steps be taken to remove travel restrictions on
                            marines in uniform.</p>
                        <p>[No reply has been received?] to previous oral representations.</p>
                        <p>The British Embassy on June 30 took the matter up orally with the Foreign
                            Office. While no reply was received, the comment of the official who was
                            interviewed was unfavorable.</p>
                        <p>Sent to the Department via Peiping. Peiping please repeat to Tientsin,
                            Shanghai, Chungking.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>